https://roomi-fields.com/en/articles/b3-derivation-rules/

Dans les r=C3=A8gles de d=C3=A9rivation que tu as document=C3=A9es, je vois =
quelques=20
probl=C3=A8mes :

1) Le mode LIN n=E2=80=99a rien =C3=A0 voir avec une d=C3=A9rivation cycliq=
ue. D=C3=A9finition=20
(selon BP3 help) :
A "subgrammar" using (context-sensitive) leftmost derivation in=20
"production", and (context-sensitive) rightmost derivation in analysis.

En fait, tout est d=C3=A9crit dans :
https://bolprocessor.org/misc/docs/
(voir la page =E2=80=9CBP2 grammars=E2=80=9D)
-- "RND" mode: rules are applied in a random order. (Default mode)
-- "LIN" mode: candidate rule chosen randomly among rules yielding a=20
leftmost derivation.
-- "ORD" mode: candidate rules are applied in the order in which they=20
appear in the grammar.
-- "SUB" mode: same as "RND", but all occurrences of the selected rule's=20
left argument in the work string are rewritten simultaneously. In this=20
mode, for instance, p-substitutions and other kinds of automatic=20
(infinite) sequences may be generated. These derivations stop either=20
when a predefined buffer length has been reached, or the weights of all=20
candidate rules are null as the result of having been dynamically=20
decremented during computation.
-- "SUB1" mode: same as "SUB", but only one rewriting of variables will=20
be allowed. This mode is much faster than "SUB" and may be used when it=20
is certain that the first substitution yields only terminal symbols.

2) Je ne comprends pas pourquoi tu as chang=C3=A9 la notation, ex. =E2=80=
=9C-mo.LIN=E2=80=9D=20
au lieu de =E2=80=9CLIN=E2=80=9D

3) Les exemples empruntant le vocabulaire du tabla sont mal choisis, et=20
musicalement incorrects pour la plupart. Il vaudrait mieux utiliser un=20
alphabet =E2=80=9Cneutre=E2=80=9D de terminaux comme a, b, c=E2=80=A6

Par exemple, le tihai n=E2=80=99est pas un cas d=E2=80=99utilisation de SUB=
, sauf si on=20
le r=C3=A9duit =C3=A0 une liste simple de phrases pr=C3=A9compos=C3=A9es. I=
l utilise une=20
grammaire et les r=C3=A9p=C3=A9tions sont r=C3=A9alis=C3=A9es par des expre=
ssions=20
parenth=C3=A9s=C3=A9es, exemple :
(=3D A)(=3D Gap)(: A)(: Gap)(: A)

Remarque : dans la grammaire =E2=80=9C-gr.dhadhatite", on utilise des symbo=
les=20
=E2=80=98+=E2=80=99 qui n=E2=80=99ont aucun usage sonore mais qui servent c=
omme contextes afin=20
de positionner certains motifs dans les templates. C=E2=80=99est utile quan=
d on=20
fait l=E2=80=99analyse de mani=C3=A8re d=C3=A9terministe (=C3=A0 suivre)=E2=
=80=A6


