=A9finition (selon BP3 help) :</div><div><i>A "subgrammar" using (context-s=
ensitive) leftmost derivation in "production", and<span>=C2=A0(context-sens=
itive) rightmost derivation in analysis.</span></i></div><div><br /></div><=
div>En fait, tout est d=C3=A9crit dans :</div><div><a href=3D"https://bolpr=
ocessor.org/misc/docs/">https://bolprocessor.org/misc/docs/</a></div><div>(=
voir la page =E2=80=9CBP2 grammars=E2=80=9D)</div><div><i>-- "RND" mode: ru=
les are applied in a random order. (Default mode)</i></div><div><i>-- "LIN" =
mode: candidate rule chosen randomly among rules yielding a leftmost deriv=
ation.</i></div><div><i>-- "ORD" mode: candidate rules are applied in the o=
rder in which they appear in the grammar.</i></div><div><i>-- "SUB" mode: s=
ame as "RND", but all occurrences of the selected rule's left argument in t=
he work string are rewritten simultaneously. In this mode, for instance, p-=
substitutions and other kinds of automatic (infinite) sequences may be gene=
rated. These derivations stop either when a predefined buffer length has be=
en reached, or the weights of all candidate rules are null as the result of =
having been dynamically decremented during computation.</i></div><div><i>-=
- "SUB1" mode: same as "SUB", but only one rewriting of variables will be a=
llowed. This mode is much faster than "SUB" and may be used when it is cert=
ain that the first substitution yields only terminal symbols.=C2=A0</i></di=
v><div><br /></div><div>2) Je ne comprends pas pourquoi tu as chang=C3=A9 l=
a notation, ex. =E2=80=9C-mo.LIN=E2=80=9D au lieu de =E2=80=9CLIN=E2=80=9D<=
/div><div><br /></div><div>3) Les exemples empruntant le vocabulaire du tab=
la sont mal choisis, et musicalement incorrects pour la plupart. Il vaudrai=
t mieux utiliser un alphabet =E2=80=9Cneutre=E2=80=9D de terminaux comme a, =
b, c=E2=80=A6</div><div><br /></div><div>Par exemple, le tihai n=E2=80=99e=
st pas un cas d=E2=80=99utilisation de SUB, sauf si on le r=C3=A9duit =C3=
=A0 une liste simple de phrases pr=C3=A9compos=C3=A9es. Il utilise une gram=
maire et les r=C3=A9p=C3=A9tions sont r=C3=A9alis=C3=A9es par des expressio=
ns parenth=C3=A9s=C3=A9es, exemple :</div><div>(=3D A)(=3D Gap)(: A)(: Gap)=
